    <div class="g12 mt36">
      <div class="pipeline reveal">
        <div class="pipe-step"><div class="pipe-num">1</div><div><h5>Phase-stratified repeated cross-sections</h5><p>Data organized into five pandemic phases, enabling structured comparison while avoiding false longitudinal claims.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pipe-step"><div class="pipe-num">2</div><div><h5>Graphical model estimation</h5><p>Per-phase symptom network via Gaussian graphical model (graphical LASSO), conditional dependence among 47 MHQ symptoms.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pipe-step"><div class="pipe-num">3</div><div><h5>Community detection &amp; domain alignment</h5><p>Weighted Louvain identifies communities, aligned to a fixed four-domain mapping for non-circular cross-phase interpretation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pipe-step"><div class="pipe-num">4</div><div><h5>Exact minimum dominating sets &amp; control metrics</h5><p>All minimum-cardinality dominating sets enumerated exactly, yielding CF, ACF, and AMCS.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pipe-step"><div class="pipe-num">5</div><div><h5>Resampling, case-dropping &amp; replication</h5><p>Bootstrap variation, case-loss stability, and India cohort replication to separate robust signals from noise.</p></div></div>
      </div>
