<!-- 7 SIGNIFICANCE -->
<section id="significance" class="sec">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="reveal"><div class="sec-label">Why This Matters</div><h2 class="sec-title">Review-worthiness at a glance.</h2></div>
    <div class="g3 stagger mt36 reveal">
      <div class="sig-card"><div class="sig-cat">Substantive</div><h4>System organization, not just prevalence</h4><p>Reframes youth mental health under prolonged crisis from symptom burden to system architecture, reaching beyond pandemic-period description.</p></div>
      <div class="sig-card"><div class="sig-cat">Methodological</div><h4>Module control with exact enumeration</h4><p>An interpretable framework, exact dominating-set enumeration, and direct metric robustness comparison for network mental health research.</p></div>
      <div class="sig-card"><div class="sig-cat">Translational</div><h4>Phase-tailored intervention targets</h4><p>Control is concentrated early but distributes as crisis becomes chronic, suggesting phase-tailored strategies over a fixed response.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt36 reveal">
      <h3 style="font-size:clamp(1.1rem,1.3vw,1.3rem);margin-bottom:16px">What this paper does not claim</h3>
      <div class="accord-item"><button class="accord-trigger">Not within-person longitudinal <i class="accord-icon">+</i></button><div class="accord-body"><div class="accord-content">Repeated cross-sections, not a cohort tracked over time. Phase comparisons describe population-level shifts, not individual trajectories.</div></div></div>
      <div class="accord-item"><button class="accord-trigger">Edges ≠ causal direction <i class="accord-icon">+</i></button><div class="accord-body"><div class="accord-content">Conditional dependencies from cross-sectional data. They do not imply that one symptom causes another.</div></div></div>
      <div class="accord-item"><button class="accord-trigger">Policy associations are exploratory <i class="accord-icon">+</i></button><div class="accord-body"><div class="accord-content">Macro-level analyses linking symptoms to policy variables are hypothesis-generating, not confirmatory.</div></div></div>
      <div class="accord-item"><button class="accord-trigger">Domain mapping is interpretive <i class="accord-icon">+</i></button><div class="accord-body"><div class="accord-content">The four-domain alignment is a fixed interpretive layer for cross-phase comparability, not an ontological claim.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

